n thickness measurements, area of isopach contours, integration limit for the power-law fit and deposit density result in ESP uncertainties ≤±20{\%} for plume height and erupted volume/mass. Finally, a third case study has also been used to explore the sensitivity of the Voronoi Tessellation strategy for the determination of TGSD and the inversion on both mass/area and grain-size data for the determination of erupted mass and plume height. Results confirm the validity of the methods but also the strong dependence on the distribution and number of observations.},
