ght of 30±3km. Results from the uncertainty analysis compare well with results from other approaches. Finally, although the climactic phase of the 2450BP Plinian eruption of Pululagua occurred in relatively calm atmospheric conditions, our results show that the dispersion of the BF2 layer was influenced by slight northeasterly wind conditions.},
